title: Taimane Levu
text:
Taimane Levu (born 25 May 1997) is an Australian <a href="rugby%20league">rugby league</a> footballer who primarily plays as a for the <a href="New%20Zealand%20Warriors">New Zealand Warriors</a> in the <a href="NRL%20Women%27s%20Premiership">NRL Women's Premiership</a> and <a href="Wests%20Panthers">Wests Panthers</a> in the <a href="QRL%20Women%27s%20Premiership">QRL Women's Premiership</a>.
Background.
Levu was born in <a href="Brisbane%2C%20Queensland">Brisbane, Queensland</a> and played her junior rugby league for the Inala Panthers.
Playing career.
In May 2019, Levu represented South East Queensland at the Women's National Championships. On 22 June 2019, Levu represented <a href="Samoa%20women%27s%20national%20rugby%20league%20team">Fetu Samoa</a> in their 46–8 loss to <a href="Kiwi%20Ferns">New Zealand</a>. On 11 October 2019, she started at prop for the <a href="Prime%20Minister%27s%20XIII">Prime Minister's XIII</a> in their win over Fiji.
2020.
In 2020, Levu played for Ipswich Brothers in the <a href="QRL%20Women%27s%20Premiership">QRL Women's Premiership</a> and later played for the <a href="Wests%20Panthers">Wests Panthers</a> in the Holcim Cup.
On 18 September, Levu joined the <a href="New%20Zealand%20Warriors">New Zealand Warriors</a> <a href="NRL%20Women%27s%20Premiership">NRL Women's Premiership</a> team. In Round 1 of the <a href="2020%20NRLW%20season">2020 NRLW season</a>, she made her debut for the Warriors in a 28–14 loss to the <a href="Brisbane%20Broncos">Brisbane Broncos</a>.
